Log in as a user

1. Log in with your username and password and click the login button.

2. Now you are on the home page.

Failed log in as a user

1. Log in with your username and password and click the login button.

2. A toast appears, if the credentials were wrong.

Log out as a user

1. Log in with your username and password and click the login button.

2. Now you are on the home page.

3. Log out of the application by clicking the LOGOUT button in the toolbar.

4. You are now logged out of the application

Create a rhythm by text

A rhythm represents a sequential arrangement of hits and pauses. This creates a beat. It has no defined meter, so the interpration for playing must be done by the user. For example a rhythm with length 12 can be seen as a 3/4 beat with sixteenth notes or a 12/8 beat with eight notes.

Recipe:

1. Log in with your username and password and click the login button.

2. Click the circled plus button in the bottom right corner.

3. Select the text option from the radio button group and click the continue button.

4. Input the text to use for the rhythm into the text field.

5. Save the rhythm by clicking the SAVE button.

6. You are left back at the home page. The new saved rhythm is now in the list.

Create a rhythm by random generation

1. Log in with your username and password and click the login button.

2. Click the circled plus button in the bottom right corner.

3. Select the random option from the radio button group and click the continue button.

4. Give the new rhythm a name by typing it into the input field.

5. Specify the length of the rhythm by adjusting the slider or typing it into the input field.

6. Make a new random rhythm by clicking the REROLL button.

7. Save the random rhythm by clicking the SAVE button.
